cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.PL

The paper deals with satisfiability checking for a logic that contains fixpoint operators and modalities, which are topics typically studied in the areas of logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Buchi games to characterize satisfiability also suggests a connection to the area of automata theory and formal languages (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions that the logic contains fragments of concurrent propositional dynamic logic (CPDL) and game logic, which are topics studied in the areas of logic and game theory (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL).
